@rdblue there are some changes over here which are not specific to #217, and there are a couple more unrelated changes I'd like to point out[1]. Let  me know if you'd like it to club it as part of this PR or make those changes as part of a separate PR and keep this PR specific to dependency exclusion. My fine both ways, if we club it as part of this PR we can update the summary in #217 and this PR

[1]. Some other changes I'd like to add
 - In Presto-runtime we are excluding guava. I think we should include and shade it.

@rdblue oh, that makes sense indeed. My assumption was that the generated output by Iceberg should be parsable by Iceberg so we could recover effective values and type of the internal partitions based on the output of `toHumanString` that Iceberg uses to generate file paths with.
Moving it to a hive specific module/ class would work best I guess :)
Closing PR.

